        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: support baseURL alias in memory embedding provider config resolution",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen users configure `models.providers.openai.baseURL` (capital `URL`) for a local or OpenAI-compatible embedding endpoint, the strict provider schema used to reject/drop that alias instead of exposing the canonical `baseUrl` field downstream.\n\nFixes #93396.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/config/zod-schema.core.ts` | Accept `models.providers.*.baseURL`, normalize it to canonical `baseUrl`, and delete the alias before downstream code reads the provider config. Existing `baseUrl` wins if both are present. |\n| `src/config/schema.test.ts` | Covers `baseURL` normalization and alias deletion, including the precedence case where canonical `baseUrl` is already set. |\n| `src/agents/memory-search.ts` | Keeps the direct built-in memory adapter when one exists. The OpenAI memory adapter already reads canonical provider `baseUrl`, so routing should stay on the existing adapter instead of becoming an unconfigured provider. |\n| `src/agents/memory-search.test.ts` | Strengthens the `baseURL` coverage so schema-normalized config must still resolve the built-in OpenAI memory adapter and its default model. |\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** `models.providers.openai.baseURL` is accepted by the production schema, normalized to `baseUrl`, then used by the real OpenAI memory embedding path to call the configured `/v1/embeddings` endpoint.\n\n**Exact commands run after fix:**\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/schema.test.ts src/agents/memory-search.test.ts\nnode --import tsx /Users/yangjiajun/projects/auto-pr/workspace/openclaw/outputs/issue-93396-pr-93505/verify-baseurl-endpoint.mjs\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence:**\n\n```text\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 6.39s\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests       94 passed (94)\n```\n\nThe endpoint proof starts a local HTTP server, parses config through `OpenClawSchema`, registers the real OpenAI memory adapter, resolves memory search config, and calls `embedBatch`.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schemaDeletedBaseURLAlias\": true,\n  \"resolvedProvider\": \"openai\",\n  \"resolvedModel\": \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n  \"adapterProviderId\": \"openai\",\n  \"request\": {\n    \"method\": \"POST\",\n    \"url\": \"/v1/embeddings\",\n    \"authorization\": \"Bearer <redacted>\",\n    \"contentType\": \"application/json\",\n    \"model\": \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n    \"inputCount\": 2\n  },\n  \"vectors\": [\n    [0.1, 0.2, 0.3],\n    [1.1, 1.2, 1.3]\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Observed result:** The alias is removed after schema normalization, memory search resolves the OpenAI built-in adapter with `text-embedding-3-small`, and the real embedding request hits the configured `/v1/embeddings` route rather than falling back to an unconfigured path.\n\n**Live service note:** This environment does not have Ollama installed or listening on `127.0.0.1:11434`, so the proof uses a local OpenAI-compatible HTTP endpoint. It still exercises the production schema, memory-search resolution, OpenAI memory adapter, and real `/v1/embeddings` HTTP request path.\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93396-Bug----Provider-name--openai",
